Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.01,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Intro}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Cat
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.58,0:00:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All things in creation correspond.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.94,0:00:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our own physical selves are each a tiny cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.06,0:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we constitute a tiny piece of a corresponding greater cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.10,0:00:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the quest to see beyond our realm, \Nthe first tool humans took up was the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.60,0:00:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The image reflected in a mirror is false,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.64,0:00:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but the mirror gives you a glimpse into a world that corresponds with your true selves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.48,0:00:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why human societies across the world have long venerated mirrors as avatars of the divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.06,0:00:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo! Tell 'em, Professor Great Big Ben London Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.10,0:01:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Lord El-Melloi II. At least put some thought into a nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.22,0:01:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine! It corresponds with his true self plenty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.64,0:01:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Flatt Escardos.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.36,0:01:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.12,0:01:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What is popular nomenclature for the act of renaming a target
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.68,0:01:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,without their knowledge or approval to exert an influence on their nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.86,0:01:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a curse, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.02,0:01:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Denouncing the god worshiped by a rival nation as a demon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.62,0:01:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}or damaging a politician's credibility by referring to him \Nwith an insulting nickname, would be two examples!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.04,0:01:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you would, Svin Glascheit,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.06,0:01:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}please explain to the class how the hogwash that left \NMr. Escardos' lips relates to the concept of correlation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.58,0:01:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.56,0:01:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Flatt's penchant for making up stupid nicknames for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.10,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attempt to elevate your status to a greater level through positive correlation, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.68,0:01:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}However, the level of corresponding greatness is constrained \Nby Flatt's own woefully lacking mental capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.68,0:01:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.70,0:01:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely. And as a result, \Nmy true nature remains unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A shadow reflected in a mirror may correspond with the true nature of its projection,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.46,0:01:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will forever fall short of its original.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.94,0:02:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, the interference of a shadow can make it possible for a target's true nature to be overwritten.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the very essence of a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.88,0:02:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.56,0:02:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we may think of magecraft as the sole technology through which our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.62,0:02:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a mere shadow of the Root, can be altered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:19.19,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, what a masterful lecture. Succinct and easily grasped.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.50,0:02:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Lord El-Melloi II.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.62,0:02:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.78,0:02:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, it was in every respect rudimentary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's disgraceful how we permit those ignorant of such fundamental concepts to call themselves magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.16,0:02:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, that's what comes of Modern Magecraft Theory \Nopening its doors to all seekers of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.14,0:02:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond me why it's considered necessary, mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.32,0:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I, for one, found it quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.56,0:03:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Great Big Ben London Star,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.32,0:03:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My distinguished colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.86,0:03:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As you well know, I am a very busy man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.88,0:03:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you came to chat, kindly save it for the next faculty tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How many years does this make it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,since you took over the El-Melloi Classroom after the former Lord's untimely death,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.48,0:03:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver Velvet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This year will make ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.72,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and ten years as well since my younger sister Sola-Ui
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}and her betrothed—Kayneth, your master—\Nmet their deaths in the Fourth Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How busy you've been, besmirching our institution with a circus of hooligans
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and herding them into the \NModern Magecraft Theory Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.24,0:03:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What a splendid little fiefdom you've built from a subject that only existed on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.60,0:03:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You flatter me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.86,0:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel scarcely worthy of such high praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, and it truly pains me to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.56,0:04:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}there are those among us who have voiced their concerns \Nabout the course you are charting with your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Lord only until Lady Reines comes of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.64,0:04:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A simple substitute, nothing more than a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I am well aware of my position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't doubt that. We all know you to be a sensible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.82,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be going now, dear brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do give my regards to your sweet little apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.78,0:04:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.84,0:04:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Back again, you mangy beast?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.76,0:04:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. It was I who fed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:04:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not at fault, Gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.70,0:05:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What do you think you're doing with your filthy paws on my sofa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get down this instant, you brainless moggy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You bloody—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.14,0:05:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you're back...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it 'til I've had my cigar, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Worthless bastards, the lot of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.44,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Beg your pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Those fossils on the faculty, trying to badger me into declaring some clear allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegiance, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.10,0:05:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Clock Tower magus is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.08,0:05:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Constantly at all the others' throats, scrapping for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Department is a pawn to them, and they're eager to know whose side of the board it's on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to force me to show my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be taking up arms against someone, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.30,0:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.56,0:06:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm but the acting Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.64,0:06:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In my position, I lack the power \Nto go toe to toe with the likes of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had the free time to waste hatching conspiracies,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd much rather devote it to my own research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.70,0:06:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike that pack of wizened bloody goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse them all! Any magus so blind to the spirit of inquiry can fall straight into the bowels of hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.84,0:06:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By the by, Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Willes from Spiritual Evocation says he really needs those reports from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the blazes didn't you tell me that sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.94,0:06:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry. You said for me to leave it 'til you'd had your cigar, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.76,0:06:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fault is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get going, Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Milady Gray... your scent is just as ravishingly graceful, yet just as deliciously cool as ever today!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.28,0:06:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Flatt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can almost see your tail start wagging \Nwhenever you and Gray cross paths, Le Chien.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.98,0:07:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask me, our Professor's the most adorable of the pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's like comparing the fragrance of a fine perfume to the smell of a grilling steak. Practically pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.22,0:07:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one's the steak here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Flatt!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...I smell the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.30,0:07:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you all right, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.92,0:07:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ahold of yourself! It's only a flesh wound!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.54,0:07:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They got me. Hit me head-on with a counter-curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard me curse them, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.08,0:07:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse them all! Any magus so blind to the spirit of inquiry can fall straight into the bowels of hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Paltry name-calling though it might have been,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.40,0:07:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,these Clock Tower ghouls would never pass up a chance to direct a curse back at its caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.68,0:07:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fucking pissants. This overcoat was brand new.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.48,0:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can dust it off for you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See that you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:07:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I do apologize, but I have somewhere to be. Clean up this—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.10,0:08:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.70,0:08:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You all right there, o venerable Professor Absolute Territory Magician?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just fine! I'd be even better if you'd quit it with the stupid nicknames!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a term of my admiration, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it so much worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.50,0:08:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think he'd have liked that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.94,0:08:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He got fourth on that "Professors that should lose the pants" poll, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.84,0:08:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst part of this is that you're utterly serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.92,0:08:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Bleeding hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's swelling something fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch it, you miserable malkin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.08,0:08:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me the anodyne herbs from that shelf over there, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.86,0:08:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Clock Tower's positively lousy with Lords,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but I daresay this is the only one hopping around tenderfooted
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,after his own mudslinging backfired!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Add!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.32,0:08:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No more of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.46,0:08:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider myself lucky that I only grazed an automatic defense mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.48,0:09:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what happened, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.46,0:09:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of it like tripping an alarm system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.66,0:09:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's most likely none of them even consciously realized I'd cursed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.92,0:09:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheeky devil! Get back here—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.82,0:09:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,With buffoonery like this, who needs the circus?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.30,0:09:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you quite all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.14,0:09:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite important to you, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.56,0:09:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.54,0:09:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent my first pay packet from the Clock Tower on those shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.42,0:09:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get them polished for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Might not be able to get all the scuffs out, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Master, I've brought the herbs for you—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.12,0:09:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:09:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to research what magecraft I can use to fix that cat's wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be a useful spell in here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only my advice, Master, but I think you'd better not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you up all last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.94,0:10:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not all night. I fell asleep in the middle of a tome of sacred treasties of the tenth century.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. I saw that when I came in to wake you and toweled off your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.66,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no lectures today or tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.34,0:10:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.06,0:10:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.16,0:10:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is too horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing \Ngetting run over out here, you fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a stray, then act like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Spare a thought for the trouble you'd cause for us humans if you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.22,0:11:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have at least had the good grace to have your accident in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.84,0:11:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumor has it Lord El-Melloi II shut himself into his chambers cradling some stray cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to confirm that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard right. Why should a first-rate instructor like you concern himself with what the rumors say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If what he's dabbling in needs a living sacrifice, a black cat is a laughably obvious choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.26,0:11:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite the contrary. If I know my brother, \Nhe's taken the cat in purely out of sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.96,0:12:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Sympathy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.10,0:12:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A magus, never mind a Lord, \Nindulging in such menial sentimentality?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a poor joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.28,0:12:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us magi are what you could call "normal".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at it that way, there's none whose conduct more befits the name of a magus than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.22,0:12:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you please have something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see this through first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.60,0:12:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do change your clothes then, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.76,0:12:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours are still wet, and the stains must be setting in something frightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.42,0:12:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.20,0:13:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.34,0:13:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Those nights without sleep are catching up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I worry your sentimentality will be the death of you sometimes, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not so much difference
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,between those that walk upon the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.62,0:13:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and those what sleep within it, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that how you see this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.60,0:13:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is any difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only with those that ought to be asleep but walk the earth instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.72,0:13:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond my power to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.34,0:13:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.38,0:14:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is nothing more than a trick of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.54,0:14:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you seek the path of magecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't time to be tripped up by such trivial diversions as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.68,0:14:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you to ask any student,\NI'm sure that's what they'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were a first-rate magus, it would have been a trivial matter to heal those wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.66,0:14:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Time and again, I'm too late and too powerless to make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.02,0:14:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.94,0:14:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the slightest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.74,0:14:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the reason I'm here, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.54,0:14:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray. I don't wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that face of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.82,0:14:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To have you detest this face of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.98,0:15:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,makes me very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.34,0:15:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Gray?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.46,0:15:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. I almost thought I could hear it still—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.72,0:15:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop that. There's no need for you to get bogged down in your master's sentimentality too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.52,0:15:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I'm sure it's the cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear its cries!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.64,0:15:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.86,0:15:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.98,0:15:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A corresponding shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.18,0:15:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My word...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.18,0:15:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Send for Svin and Flatt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shade that passes across the surface of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn that rips aside the veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.82,0:15:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tracks of amber that cross between stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:15:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Return here from the twilight, and blow breath into lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.54,0:16:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the person who placed the curse on you, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.18,0:16:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To be precise, the car is the one that did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The culprit ran down the cat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.06,0:16:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,after first binding it with a curse that would transfer its agony to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So in short, since the cat has a connection to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a mortal injury to the cat could kill you as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.58,0:16:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The car and its wheels symbolize the cycle of fate, constantly turning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With the application of magecraft,\N the culprit transferred the curse to my shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.00,0:16:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the culprit did this to the cat intentionally in order to kill you, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But they miscalculated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.26,0:16:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They never accounted for the depth of Gray's ties to the realm of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.24,0:16:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If Gray hadn't picked up on the cat's presence when she did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be in much worse shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.22,0:16:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I 'spose that's the one thing she's got going for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.10,0:16:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Add!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.60,0:16:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if the curse is possessing a shadow,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.26,0:17:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the reflection of that shadow in the mirror will show you its true nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.68,0:17:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you track it by scent, Svin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.84,0:17:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, sir. But that said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't it be easiest to settle this by countercursing the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.90,0:17:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If I did that, I'd never find out who did this to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.22,0:17:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,These Clock Tower folk certainly do pay well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.10,0:17:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And no sign of a countercurse on the way, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.94,0:17:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's high time I had myself a vacation in Monaco.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Spoke too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our trusty ol' Le Chien!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk about me like some old bloodhound!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.30,0:17:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to say though, the methods this guy used are incredibly reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.10,0:17:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that the curse is cycling, it's not just affecting the Professor, it's running its course through him too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:18:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I ought to tell him that in ten years time he'll be suffering gout, diabetes, or worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell the bastard whatever you like after we catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I don't hurry up and get this sorted,\N the curse will stop my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit! Why won't you just die?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let us handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for what you did to Milady Gray's cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.68,0:18:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit yapping and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.34,0:18:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Palladia Mors!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What the blazes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fortification?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.68,0:18:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No! It's bestial magecraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.48,0:19:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Game Select!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief that you were able to apprehend the person behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.18,0:19:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That man was merely the perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,His memories were more than likely altered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.82,0:19:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In Reines' opinion, he didn't even know whose orders he was acting on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.60,0:19:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to solve the mystery of who really did it, and how,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.75,0:19:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is pointless when the culprit is a magus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.56,0:19:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But the whydunit remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.00,0:20:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not hard to imagine why \Nsomeone would want me dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.62,0:20:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a Lord, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.04,0:20:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat was just collateral damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I think that in doing this, you saved the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Any feeling of satisfaction that saving something might give you is just another trick of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.32,0:20:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping others won't improve your own lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.50,0:20:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor will you ever know for certain if the help you gave them did any good in the long run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.06,0:20:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.06,0:20:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.52,0:20:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you saved me. And that's for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.82,0:20:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you saved the cat as well. That's what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.38,0:21:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What lies within our reach is a mere conglomeration of facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.62,0:21:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The one truth lies beyond our grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Misconceptions, misunderstandings, mismatches and misapprehensions...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.50,0:21:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What an utterly foolish cycle of repetitions this world we live in is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.82,0:21:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Little more than a shadow in a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.32,0:21:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at it that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the battles I fought at your side were far simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.08,0:21:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}this place
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is my battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.48,0:21:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.06,0:21:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Adashino from Policies wants a word with me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.42,0:22:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For pity's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.82,0:22:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be going out, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.58,0:22:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.66,0:22:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like yet another nuisance needs my attention, Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.99,0:22:33.01,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{ED}
